Not valid against the MusicXML XSD.

Violation: five `<note>` elements in measure 34 are cue notes
(`<cue/>` first child) that also contain a `<tie>` child. The MusicXML
3.0 schema disallows tie inside cue notes - the `cue` branch of the
note content model is:

    cue, full-note, duration   (no tie element)

The note-type documentation in musicxml.xsd confirms this: "Cue notes
have a duration element, as do forward elements, but no tie elements."

mx::core's fromXDoc rejects the document with "Note: unexpected
element 'tie'" (5 times) - the parser is correctly enforcing the
schema.

See data/README.md for the .invalid marker convention.
